sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>(7 BFF Plugins)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant StorageInit as storage-initializer<br/>(init container)
    participant ModelPod as Model Server<br/>(vLLM/OVMS/MLServer)
    participant ODHModelCtrl as odh-model-controller
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Gateway as Gateway API<br/>(Envoy)
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Deployment via Dashboard

    User->>Dashboard: Login via IntegratedOAuth/OIDC
    Dashboard-->>User: Show project overview (gen-ai BFF)
    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService via UI form
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: POST InferenceService CR<br/>(bearer token forwarding)
    K8sAPI-->>KServe: InferenceService watch triggered
    KServe->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service,<br/>HTTPRoute, HPA/KEDA ScaledObject
    KServe->>StorageInit: Inject init container into pod spec
    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    S3-->>StorageInit: model.bin + config.json
    StorageInit-->>ModelPod: Model ready in shared volume
    Note over ModelPod: Model server starts,<br/>loads model into memory
    ODHModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy,<br/>ServiceMonitor for pod
    ODHModelCtrl->>Prometheus: Register scrape target
    ModelReg->>KServe: Sync InferenceService status<br/>to registry metadata
    KServe->>Gateway: Configure HTTPRoute<br/>for external access

    Note over Client,Gateway: Production inference begins
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/my-model:predict<br/>(HTTPS/443, Bearer Token)
    Gateway->>ModelPod: Forward request via HTTPRoute
    ModelPod-->>Gateway: Prediction result (JSON)
    Gateway-->>Client: Response (HTTPS)

    User->>Dashboard: View model metrics + status
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Query InferenceService status
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: Get model metadata<br/>(model-registry BFF)
    Dashboard-->>User: Model health, latency, throughput

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Gateway API<br/>(Envoy)
    participant AIGW as ai-gateway-payload-processing<br/>(ext-proc)
    participant EPP as EPP<br/>(llm-d-inference-scheduler)
    participant VLLM as vLLM Pod<br/>(llm-d stack)
    participant GuardOrch as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(regex, ML, LLM judge)
    participant NeMo as NeMo Guardrails
    participant WVA as WVA Controller
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Workflow 2: LLM Inference with Guardrails (llm-d Stack)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443, OpenAI-compatible)
    Gateway->>AIGW: ext-proc: ProcessingRequest
    Note over AIGW: Resolve model name,<br/>translate API format,<br/>inject provider credentials
    AIGW-->>Gateway: Modified request
    Gateway->>EPP: ext-proc: Route selection
    Note over EPP: Run scheduling plugins:<br/>KV-cache scorer,<br/>saturation filter,<br/>profile handler
    EPP-->>Gateway: Selected target vLLM pod
    Gateway->>VLLM: Forward to optimal pod<br/>(KV-cache aware routing)

    alt Guardrails Enabled
        VLLM->>GuardOrch: Route through guardrails pipeline
        GuardOrch->>Detectors: Dispatch to detection backends
        Detectors-->>GuardOrch: Detection results
        GuardOrch->>NeMo: Content safety check
        NeMo-->>GuardOrch: Safety verdict
        GuardOrch-->>VLLM: Approved/blocked response
    end

    VLLM-->>Gateway: Chat completion response<br/>(streaming SSE or JSON)
    Gateway-->>Client: Response (HTTPS)

    Note over WVA,Prometheus: Autoscaling loop (continuous)
    WVA->>Prometheus: Query KV-cache utilization,<br/>queue depth metrics
    Prometheus-->>WVA: Current metrics
    Note over WVA: Apply queueing theory models,<br/>calculate target replicas
    WVA->>VLLM: Adjust replica count<br/>via HPA/KEDA metrics

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>(pipeline UI)
    participant KFPSDK as KFP SDK<br/>(kfp.Client)
    participant DSPAPI as DSP API Server
    participant ArgoCtrl as Argo Workflows<br/>Controller
    participant Driver as DSP Driver
    participant Launcher as DSP Launcher
    participant S3 as S3/SeaweedFS<br/>(Artifact Store)
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata DB
    participant PersistAgent as DSP Persistence<br/>Agent

    Note over User,PersistAgent: Workflow 3: Data Science Pipeline Execution

    alt Via Dashboard
        User->>Dashboard: Submit pipeline run via UI
        Dashboard->>DSPAPI: POST pipeline run<br/>(bearer token forwarding)
    else Via SDK
        User->>KFPSDK: kfp.Client().create_run()
        KFPSDK->>DSPAPI: POST pipeline run<br/>(SA token or user token)
    end

    DSPAPI->>DSPAPI: Store pipeline spec in DB
    DSPAPI->>ArgoCtrl: Create Argo Workflow CR
    ArgoCtrl->>ArgoCtrl: Parse DAG, create pod<br/>per pipeline step

    loop For each pipeline step
        ArgoCtrl->>Driver: Launch driver container
        Note over Driver: Resolve inputs,<br/>evaluate conditions,<br/>check cache
        Driver->>Launcher: Generate pod patches,<br/>launch user code container
        Launcher->>Launcher: Execute user code
        Launcher->>S3: Upload output artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
        Launcher->>MLMD: Publish execution metadata
    end

    PersistAgent->>ArgoCtrl: Watch Workflow status
    PersistAgent->>DSPAPI: Persist run results to DB

    User->>Dashboard: View pipeline run results
    Dashboard->>DSPAPI: GET run details + artifacts
    Dashboard-->>User: Pipeline visualization,<br/>metrics, artifact links

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant NotebookCtrl as Kubeflow Notebook<br/>Controller
    participant Notebook as JupyterLab Workbench<br/>(StatefulSet)
    participant TrainingHub as training-hub SDK
    participant Trainer as Kubeflow Trainer<br/>(v2 controller)
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller
    participant TrainingPods as Training Pods<br/>(distributed)
    participant Kueue as Kueue
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard

    Note over User,Dashboard: Workflow 4: Notebook-to-Training Pipeline

    User->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR via Dashboard
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Create StatefulSet with:<br/>GPU/CPU resources,<br/>kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>Feast config injection
    Note over Notebook: JupyterLab workbench ready

    User->>Notebook: Develop model code
    Notebook->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    Note over Notebook: Local prototyping +<br/>experimentation

    User->>TrainingHub: Submit distributed training<br/>via training-hub SDK
    TrainingHub->>Trainer: Create TrainJob CR +<br/>TrainingRuntime selection
    Trainer->>Trainer: Reconcile TrainJob:<br/>apply Torch/MPI/TorchTune<br/>plugin configurations
    Trainer->>JobSet: Create JobSet resource
    JobSet->>Kueue: Request resource quota<br/>(gang-scheduling PodGroup)
    Kueue-->>JobSet: Quota approved
    JobSet->>TrainingPods: Create distributed<br/>training pods

    loop Training execution
        TrainingPods->>S3: Read training data,<br/>write checkpoints<br/>(HTTPS/443)
        TrainingPods->>TrainingPods: Distributed gradient sync
    end

    Trainer->>TrainingPods: Poll HTTP metrics<br/>for real-time progress
    Trainer->>Trainer: Store progress in<br/>TrainJob annotations

    User->>Dashboard: View training progress
    Dashboard->>Trainer: Query TrainJob status
    Dashboard-->>User: Training metrics,<br/>loss curves, ETA

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>(eval-hub-ui BFF)
    participant EvalHubAPI as EvalHub API
    participant EvalJob as Evaluation Job<br/>(lm-eval/RAGAS/Garak)
    participant ModelEndpoint as Target Model<br/>(KServe endpoint)
    participant MLflow as MLflow<br/>(Experiment Tracking)
    participant OCIReg as OCI Registry<br/>(Result Artifacts)
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Operator<br/>(failure reconciler)
    participant Kueue as Kueue

    Note over User,Kueue: Workflow 5: Model Evaluation and Safety Scanning

    User->>Dashboard: Configure evaluation job:<br/>select model, benchmarks,<br/>evaluation providers
    Dashboard->>EvalHubAPI: POST evaluation request<br/>(eval-hub BFF, kube-rbac-proxy auth)
    EvalHubAPI->>Kueue: Submit evaluation workload<br/>(resource quota check)
    Kueue-->>EvalHubAPI: Quota approved
    EvalHubAPI->>EvalJob: Create evaluation Job in<br/>tenant namespace with:<br/>eval-runtime-sidecar,<br/>init container

    loop Per evaluation backend
        EvalJob->>ModelEndpoint: Execute benchmarks against<br/>model endpoint (HTTPS)
        ModelEndpoint-->>EvalJob: Model predictions
        Note over EvalJob: Compute evaluation metrics<br/>(accuracy, latency, safety)
    end

    EvalJob->>OCIReg: Upload results as<br/>OCI artifacts (HTTPS/443)
    EvalJob->>EvalHubAPI: POST evaluation callback<br/>(results summary)
    EvalHubAPI->>MLflow: Record results in<br/>MLflow experiment tracking
    EvalHubAPI->>EvalHubAPI: Aggregate scores<br/>across providers

    alt Job failure (OOM, image pull error)
        TrustyAI->>EvalJob: Detect operator-only failure<br/>(crashed container cannot self-report)
        TrustyAI->>EvalHubAPI: Report structured<br/>failure event
    end

    User->>Dashboard: View evaluation results
    Dashboard->>EvalHubAPI: GET evaluation results
    Dashboard->>MLflow: GET experiment data<br/>(mlflow BFF)
    Dashboard-->>User: Evaluation dashboard:<br/>scores, comparisons,<br/>safety verdicts
